  <article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">
    <h1>About SmartPetGuide</h1>

    <p>SmartPetGuide was founded in 2026 by a team of pet owners tired of sifting through fake reviews and AI-generated fluff. We spend weeks testing each product with real dogs and cats — no lab conditions, no manufacturer samples, just real-world use in real homes.</p>

    <h2>Our Story</h2>
    <p>Like most pet owners, we started as overwhelmed shoppers. Which $600 litter box is actually worth it? Does a $89 automatic feeder work as well as a $139 one? The internet was full of contradictory advice, sponsored posts disguised as reviews, and "best of" lists written by people who clearly never owned a pet.</p>
    <p>So we decided to fix that. SmartPetGuide is the site we wish existed when we were shopping — honest comparisons, real testing, and clear recommendations based on evidence, not affiliate commissions.</p>

    <h2>How We Test</h2>
    <p>Every product we review goes through a rigorous evaluation:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Real-world testing (2+ weeks):</strong> Each device lives in a home with actual pets — cats and dogs of different sizes, ages, and temperaments. We test with multiple pets where applicable.</li>
      <li><strong>App & connectivity testing:</strong> We evaluate companion apps on both iOS and Android, testing Wi-Fi reliability, scheduling accuracy, notification speed, and overall user experience over days of continuous use.</li>
      <li><strong>User review aggregation:</strong> We analyze thousands of verified purchase reviews across Amazon and other retailers to identify patterns — when 500 people report the same motor failure, we flag it.</li>
      <li><strong>Cost-of-ownership analysis:</strong> Upfront price is only part of the story. We calculate 3-year total costs including replacement filters, disposable trays, subscription fees, and typical lifespan.</li>
      <li><strong>Comparative testing:</strong> Whenever possible, we test competing products side-by-side in the same environment to give you the most honest A vs B assessment.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Why Trust Us?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Independent:</strong> We are not owned by any pet brand, retailer, or manufacturer. Our recommendations are based on testing, not partnerships.</li>
      <li><strong>Transparent:</strong> Every article clearly discloses our affiliate relationships. We earn commissions from qualifying Amazon purchases — at zero cost to you.</li>
      <li><strong>Evidence-based:</strong> We cite real Amazon review counts, Best Sellers Ranks, and verified purchase data. No vague "we loved it" statements without specifics.</li>
      <li><strong>Updated:</strong> All articles carry a 2026 date stamp and are regularly updated when new models launch or prices change.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Our Testing Team</h2>
    <p>Our reviews are written and fact-checked by pet owners who collectively have tested 50+ smart pet devices. Our testers include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>A multi-cat household running two Litter-Robots and three automatic feeders simultaneously</li>
      <li>A Golden Retriever owner testing GPS trackers on daily off-leash hikes</li>
      <li>A tech-forward cat owner evaluating app-controlled fountains and health-monitoring litter boxes</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Make Money</h2>
    <p>SmartPetGuide participates in the Amazon Associates program. When you click our links and buy a product, we earn a small commission — typically 3-5% of the purchase price. This costs you nothing extra and directly funds our testing. We also plan to join additional affiliate networks (ShareASale, Impact) to diversify our revenue.</p>
    <p><strong>Our editorial integrity promise:</strong> We never accept payment for reviews, sponsored placements, or "paid to promote" deals. Products are purchased independently. Our rankings are based on testing results, not commission rates.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions, suggestions, or a product you'd like us to test? We read every email: <a href="mailto:hello@smartpetguide.com">hello@smartpetguide.com</a></p>
  </article>
